    <!-- ═══════ §7 FAQ — HOW IT WORKS ═══════ -->
    <section id="faq-section" class="mb-10">
      <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-700/40 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-kernel-700/40 border border-kernel-700/30 flex items-center justify-center text-kernel-400 text-lg">?</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-kernel-200">How It Works — FAQ</h2>
            <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs">Plain-language answers to common questions</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4" id="faq-list">
          <details class="bg-kernel-800/40 rounded-lg border border-kernel-700/20 group">
            <summary class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-4 text-sm font-medium text-kernel-300 hover:text-kernel-100 transition-colors">
              <span class="text-kernel-600 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform">▶</span>
              What is the Cognitive Equalizer?
            </summary>
            <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-xs text-kernel-400 leading-relaxed">
              A mathematical protocol that evaluates AI responses using the same GCD kernel that analyses particle physics, atomic structure, and 21 other domains.
              It scores 8 dimensions of quality, computes structural invariants (fidelity, integrity, entropy, curvature), classifies the regime (Stable/Watch/Collapse),
              and derives a three-valued verdict. The key innovation: the verdict is <strong class="text-kernel-200">derived from frozen structure</strong>, never asserted by the agent.
              Two different AIs, given the same channel scores, MUST produce the same verdict.
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="bg-kernel-800/40 rounded-lg border border-kernel-700/20 group">
            <summary class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-4 text-sm font-medium text-kernel-300 hover:text-kernel-100 transition-colors">
              <span class="text-kernel-600 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform">▶</span>
              Why IC (geometric mean) instead of F (arithmetic mean)?
            </summary>
            <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-xs text-kernel-400 leading-relaxed">
              Averages lie. A response can have high <span class="font-mono text-green-400">F = 0.83</span> (looks good!) while having
